==English==

===Pronunciation===
*/bɔrk/, /bOrk/

=== Verb ===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|bork||}}
# To misconfigure, especially a computer or other complex device.
# To break or damage.
# To snub or disrespect.

==== Etymology ====
[[Category:Disputed etymologies]] Possibly derived from ''[[borken]]'', which is an intentional misspelling of the word ''broken''.  ''The computer is borken''.  The word is often used in ironic or humorous contexts.

=== Verb ===
# To destroy a judicial nominee through a concerted attack on his character, background and philosophy. 

==== Etymology ====
From the supreme court nomination of Robert Bork. [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Bork#.22Bork.22_as_a_verb] [http://www.iht.com/articles/1993/01/13/topi_3.php]